---
source: crates/wasm-cli/tests/test.rs
expression: output
---
Execute a Wasm Component

Usage: wasm run [OPTIONS] <INPUT>

Arguments:
  <INPUT>
          Local file path, OCI reference, or manifest key (scope:component) for a Wasm Component

Options:
      --env <KEY=VAL>
          Pass an environment variable to the guest (repeatable)

      --dir <HOST_PATH>
          Pre-open a host directory for the guest (repeatable)

      --inherit-env
          Inherit all host environment variables

      --inherit-network
          Allow the guest to access the network

      --no-stdio
          Suppress stdin/stdout/stderr inheritance

      --listen <ADDR>
          Address to bind the HTTP server to when running a `wasi:http/proxy` component
          
          [default: 127.0.0.1:8080]

  -g, --global
          Run the component directly from the global cache, bypassing the requirement that it be installed in the local project.
          
          Only meaningful when INPUT is a manifest key (`scope:component`).

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version

Global Options:
      --color <WHEN>
          When to use colored output
          
          [default: auto]
          [possible values: auto, always, never]

      --offline
          Run in offline mode

  -v, --verbose...
          Increase logging verbosity

  -q, --quiet...
          Decrease logging verbosity
